&s;ons, and one daughter.</P>
<P>1. Sir <HI>William,</HI> his heir.</P>
<P>2. <HI>Thomas Con&s;table</HI> who married Mar|garet,
daughter of &s;ir Thomas Manly,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ibid. ad ann<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">. 1410.</NOTE> knight,
and had i&s;&s;ue.</P>
<P>His daughter, <HI>Margaret,</HI> married to &s;ir John
Copledike of Harrington,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Archer's hi&s;t. of Lincoln|&s;hire, p. 73.</NOTE> <HI>in com. Lincoln.</HI>
knight, and had i&s;&s;ue.</P>
<P>He died <HI>anno</HI> 1394, and was &s;ucceeded by
his elde&s;t &s;on,</P>
<P>XI. Sir WILLIAM of Hal&s;ham, Burton-Con&s;table,
<HI>&amp;c.</HI> who, <HI>anno</HI> 1400 married E|lizabeth,
daughter of&mdash;Metham,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Burton's col.</NOTE> by
whom he had a &s;on and &s;ucce&s;&s;or,</P>
<P>XII. Sir JOHN CONSTABLE of Hal&s;ham,
<HI>&amp;c.</HI> who married Margaret, daughter and
co-heire&s;s of &s;ir Thomas Um&s;raville, knight,
